From ae74b6673d83883141cd9760073709e818e471d0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Michael Neale <michael.neale@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 4 Apr 2026 16:43:39 +1100
Subject: [PATCH 07/15] moe-split: fix shared-expert tensor corruption for
 qwen35moe and similar architectures
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Architectures with shared experts (qwen35moe, deepseek2, etc.) use
ffn_gate_inp_shexp tensors alongside the routed ffn_gate_inp tensors.
The is_router_gate() check matched both because strstr("ffn_gate_inp_shexp",
"ffn_gate_inp") returns non-null.

In the header phase this caused a dimension-mismatch warning but fell through
to copy-as-is. In the data phase it wrote truncated data, corrupting all
subsequent tensor offsets — producing shards that llama-server refused to load:
  tensor 'blk.N.ffn_up_shexp.weight' data is not within the file bounds

Add is_shared_expert() to exclude _shexp tensors from the router gate path.
Shared expert tensors are trunk and should be copied verbatim to every shard.

Backwards compatible: models without _shexp tensors (OLMoE, GLM, etc.) are
unaffected.
---
 tools/moe-split/moe-split.cpp | 9 +++++++--
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/tools/moe-split/moe-split.cpp b/tools/moe-split/moe-split.cpp
index e6a8fa84f..c950f5695 100644
--- a/tools/moe-split/moe-split.cpp
+++ b/tools/moe-split/moe-split.cpp
@@ -215,9 +215,14 @@ static bool is_expert_tensor(const char * name) {
         || strstr(name, "ffn_down_exps") != nullptr;
 }
 
-// Check if tensor is the MoE router gate
+// Check if tensor is a shared-expert tensor (trunk, not sliced)
+static bool is_shared_expert(const char * name) {
+    return strstr(name, "_shexp") != nullptr;
+}
+
+// Check if tensor is the MoE router gate (but not the shared-expert gate)
 static bool is_router_gate(const char * name) {
-    return strstr(name, "ffn_gate_inp") != nullptr;
+    return strstr(name, "ffn_gate_inp") != nullptr && !is_shared_expert(name);
 }
 
 static void zeros(std::ofstream & f, size_t n) {
